disneyland dream ( 1956 ) is a home movie made by robbins and meg barstow that documents their family 's free trip to the newly opened disneyland .   the one-week trip was a prize that they won in a contest sponsored by scotch tape .   the movie was shot with a 16 mm handheld camera . it lasts approximately 30 minutes .   an audio track was added to the film in 1995 .   the barstows lived in wethersfield , connecticut .   they flew to california with twa and stayed at the huntington sheraton hotel in pasadena .   they visited other southern california locations , including knott 's berry farm , hollywood , grauman 's chinese theatre , beverly hills , universal studios , will rogers ' home and catalina island on their july 1956 trip .   comedian steve martin who worked at disneyland as a child , appears at about twenty minutes into the film , briefly walking left to right in the lower part of the frame , dressed in top hat , vest , and pink striped shirt .